<subSubSection id="EBCDF5AB7737FFF6FF4EFE08089F48FF" pageId="12" pageNumber="393" type="description">
<paragraph id="A368A6207737FFF6FF4EFE0808664BB3" blockId="12.[151,1437,433,820]" box="[151,855,433,460]" pageId="12" pageNumber="393">
<emphasis id="91A37A327737FFF6FF4EFE080A184BB4" bold="true" box="[151,297,433,459]" pageId="12" pageNumber="393">Description.</emphasis>
Brown with indistinct dark pattern (
<figureCitation id="3BECBAA57737FFF6FD18FE08087A4BB3" box="[705,843,433,460]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–47" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1997,2021]" captionTargetBox="[176,1408,535,1967]" captionTargetId="figure-133@11.[174,1412,525,1974]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 29–47. Macropsis spp., lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4404167" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4404167/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="393">Figs. 34–35</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A368A6207737FFF6FF1EFE6C08D94824" blockId="12.[151,1437,433,820]" pageId="12" pageNumber="393">
Abdominal apodemes of 2 
<superScript id="54A20B687737FFF6FE2AFE6C09324B9C" attach="left" box="[499,515,469,483]" fontSize="6" pageId="12" pageNumber="393">nd</superScript>
tergite in male long, with strongly convergent and widened tips (
<figureCitation id="3BECBAA57737FFF6FB33FE6C0EA04B90" box="[1258,1425,469,495]" captionStart="FIGURES 165–203" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[207,1381,183,1840]" captionTargetId="figure-16@21.[205,1382,181,1843]" captionText="FIGURES 165–203. Macropsis aselae sp. n. (165–182), M. illota (183–189), M. sibirica (190–195), M. megerlei (196), M. emeljanovi (197), M. elaeagni (198–199), and M. scabrosa (200–203). 165–167, 183–184, 190–191, 198, 201―male abdominal apodemes of the 2nd tergite; 168–171, 185–186, 192, 199, 202—the 2nd sternite; 172–174, 187–188, 193–194, 196–197, 200―penis, lateral view; 175–177―pygofer process, lateral view; 178–179―style; 180–182, 189, 195, 203―the 2nd valvulae of ovipositor." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4457948" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4457948/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="393">Figs. 183–184</figureCitation>
). Sternal apodemes narrow triangular, separated by angular notch (
<figureCitation id="3BECBAA57737FFF6FCA3FE400F10486B" box="[890,1057,505,532]" captionStart="FIGURES 165–203" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[207,1381,183,1840]" captionTargetId="figure-16@21.[205,1382,181,1843]" captionText="FIGURES 165–203. Macropsis aselae sp. n. (165–182), M. illota (183–189), M. sibirica (190–195), M. megerlei (196), M. emeljanovi (197), M. elaeagni (198–199), and M. scabrosa (200–203). 165–167, 183–184, 190–191, 198, 201―male abdominal apodemes of the 2nd tergite; 168–171, 185–186, 192, 199, 202—the 2nd sternite; 172–174, 187–188, 193–194, 196–197, 200―penis, lateral view; 175–177―pygofer process, lateral view; 178–179―style; 180–182, 189, 195, 203―the 2nd valvulae of ovipositor." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4457948" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4457948/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="393">Figs. 185–186</figureCitation>
). Penis stem in side view narrow, usually, bent at almost right angle (
<figureCitation id="3BECBAA57737FFF6FDC5FDA409F04848" box="[540,705,541,567]" captionStart="FIGURES 165–203" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[207,1381,183,1840]" captionTargetId="figure-16@21.[205,1382,181,1843]" captionText="FIGURES 165–203. Macropsis aselae sp. n. (165–182), M. illota (183–189), M. sibirica (190–195), M. megerlei (196), M. emeljanovi (197), M. elaeagni (198–199), and M. scabrosa (200–203). 165–167, 183–184, 190–191, 198, 201―male abdominal apodemes of the 2nd tergite; 168–171, 185–186, 192, 199, 202—the 2nd sternite; 172–174, 187–188, 193–194, 196–197, 200―penis, lateral view; 175–177―pygofer process, lateral view; 178–179―style; 180–182, 189, 195, 203―the 2nd valvulae of ovipositor." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4457948" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4457948/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="393">Figs. 187–188</figureCitation>
). 2 
<superScript id="54A20B687737FFF6FD38FDA409C04854" attach="left" box="[737,753,541,555]" fontSize="6" pageId="12" pageNumber="393">nd</superScript>
valvulae of ovipositor with one very long and narrow preapical tooth each; sometimes one valvula has additional small tooth (
<figureCitation id="3BECBAA57737FFF6FCA0FDF808EA4824" box="[889,987,577,603]" captionStart="FIGURES 165–203" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[207,1381,183,1840]" captionTargetId="figure-16@21.[205,1382,181,1843]" captionText="FIGURES 165–203. Macropsis aselae sp. n. (165–182), M. illota (183–189), M. sibirica (190–195), M. megerlei (196), M. emeljanovi (197), M. elaeagni (198–199), and M. scabrosa (200–203). 165–167, 183–184, 190–191, 198, 201―male abdominal apodemes of the 2nd tergite; 168–171, 185–186, 192, 199, 202—the 2nd sternite; 172–174, 187–188, 193–194, 196–197, 200―penis, lateral view; 175–177―pygofer process, lateral view; 178–179―style; 180–182, 189, 195, 203―the 2nd valvulae of ovipositor." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4457948" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4457948/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="393">Fig. 189</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A368A6207737FFF6FF1EFDDC089F48FF" blockId="12.[151,1437,433,820]" box="[199,942,613,640]" pageId="12" pageNumber="393">
Body length (including tegmina): 
<specimenCount id="B5D16DA97737FFF6FD9DFDDF096A48FF" box="[580,603,614,640]" pageId="12" pageNumber="393" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
, 
<quantity id="642F0BC57737FFF6FDBEFDDC09C048FF" box="[615,753,613,640]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.75" metricValueMax="3.9" metricValueMin="3.6" pageId="12" pageNumber="393" unit="mm" value="3.75" valueMax="3.9" valueMin="3.6">3.6–3.9 mm</quantity>
; 
<specimenCount id="B5D16DA97737FFF6FD24FDDF082348FF" box="[765,786,614,640]" pageId="12" pageNumber="393" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
, 
<quantity id="642F0BC57737FFF6FCF9FDDC089B48FF" box="[800,938,613,640]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.35" metricValueMax="4.5" metricValueMin="4.2" pageId="12" pageNumber="393" unit="mm" value="4.35" valueMax="4.5" valueMin="4.2">4.2–4.5 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="EBCDF5AB7737FFF6FF1EFD300A8348DB" box="[199,434,649,676]" pageId="12" pageNumber="393" type="biology_ecology">
